<section xmlns="http://xml.house.gov/schemas/uslm/1.0" style="-uslm-lc:I80" id="idf69e3b72-2930-11f1-96a8-b9bd2a0a99b5" identifier="/us/usc/t46/s14502"><num value="14502">§ 14502.</num><heading> Measurement</heading><content>
<p style="-uslm-lc:I11" class="indent0">The Secretary shall measure a vessel to which this chapter applies in the way provided by this chapter.</p>
</content><sourceCredit id="idf69e3b73-2930-11f1-96a8-b9bd2a0a99b5">(<ref href="/us/pl/99/509/tV/s5101/3">Pub. L. 99–509, title V, § 5101(3)</ref>, <date date="1986-10-21">Oct. 21, 1986</date>, <ref href="/us/stat/100/1923">100 Stat. 1923</ref>.)</sourceCredit>
<notes type="uscNote" id="idf69e3b74-2930-11f1-96a8-b9bd2a0a99b5">
<note style="-uslm-lc:I74" topic="historicalAndRevision" id="idf69e3b75-2930-11f1-96a8-b9bd2a0a99b5"><heading class="centered smallCaps">Historical and Revision Notes</heading><p style="-uslm-lc:I580467" class="indent2 firstIndent-2 bold"><i>Revised section 14502</i></p>
<p style="-uslm-lc:I21" class="indent0">Source: Section (U.S. Code) 46 App. U.S.C. 71, 77, 83.</p>
<p style="-uslm-lc:I21" class="indent0">Section 14502 requires the Secretary to measure a vessel to which this chapter applies as provided by this chapter.</p>
</note>
</notes>
</section>
